    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-12-28T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-12-28T12:00:00-05:00" n="151"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/1034: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-28T10:00:00-07:00"
                            >December 28, 1930—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>127. Replying to your December 27, 6 p.m., Luis Chacon’s resignation as Third
                    Designado was submitted to the Legislative Assembly, on December 17, 1930, but
                    Congress had never accepted or rejected it. Palma has only resigned as
                    Provisional President.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
